reviewContent: I ordered and paid for $6 Extra Most Bestest. They said I would have to wait a few minutes, so I did. A few minutes later I got my pizza and left. I later discovered that they put a 15-20 minute old $5 pepperoni pizza in my Extra Most Bestest box. I guess that's their way of refreshing their inventory when they made too many $5 pizzas and not enough $6 pizzas. I'll be on the lookout for this now.

location: 2645 N Canyon Ranch DrCedar City, UT 84721
reviewContent: All star meals are a great deal for $5. Big hamburger is $1.99. Service was fast and food was good.

Sunday breakfast was $8.99. Not turrible, but drinks are overpriced at $2.49 so I got water. The water at one of the drink machines has a funky taste. The waitress was mostly a table busser. Food was good.
Cravings menu is  $1 as it should be. Food was good and very fast. The menu doesn't show the cravings deal or meal deals.
$6.49 for 2 fish and fries. Not turrible. I came here thinking it was only taco bell, but both restaurants are in the same building. Food was good and very fast.

location: 6605 N Indian Canyon DrPalm Springs, CA 92240
reviewContent: They have a couple $5 meals that aren't turrible, but other than that prices aren't looking so good. They don't have a self serve drink machine just like most Wendy's. Food was good and very fast.
The never ending pasta for $9.99 was a decent deal. I hardly ever eat here because it isn't cheap without that deal. The waiter was slacking on refills. The food was good as usual.
I don't eat Arby's often due to their rip off prices, but between 2 and 5 pm they have a dollar menu that's not turrible. Some of their sliders are pretty good.
All-star meals are a great deal at $5, big hamburgers are stupidly overpriced at  $2.49. Service wasn't very quick even with only 4 people in the lobby. Food was good.
No great values, but the 4 for $5.55 isn't turrible. Crisp bean burritos were good. Service was good and fast.
$5 all star meals are a great deal. Big hamburgers are $2, a little too much. Food is good and fast.
Meal deals  $2.99, cravings deal  $4.99, quesorito box  $4.99. Prices are right, food was good and fast.

One thing I don't like about Wendy's is they often don't have self serve drink machines, but this locatation does and they actually have 2 machines. They have a 4 for $4 and a $5 deal. Both great deals. Service was great and food was too.

Food is good, but the price isn't on Thursday and especially Friday and Saturday. $16.49 Thursday, $30+ Friday and Saturday. They start packing up the food at 9:15 and stop bringing drinks. I was thirsty AF. I would only recommend coming Monday-Wednesday before 8:00.
Lunch buffet is $7.99, not great, not bad. Drinks are extra. The food was good, since they don't cook too many.

category:
Fast Food,
                    Chicken Wings,
                    Chicken Shop
reviewContent: Good service, good food. The $5 meals are a decent deal, but other than that I couldn't find cheap items to chase the meal. I got a chicken little for  $1.79. Rip off.
Meal deals are 20 cents too much at $3.19, but cravings deal is priced right at  $4.99. Potatoritos were good, but about as girthy as a roll of quarters. Ridiculous. Food was good and quick.
I had the breakfast buffet on a Sunday. $10.49 with water. Price isn't great for cheap breakfast food, but pretty typical for truck stops. Food was good and service was good.
Meal deals are $3.99. Rip off. I looked for a cravings deal as a plan B, but they don't have that. Potatoritos were priced right at least at $1. Food was good and quick.
I couldn't find a cheaper burger than the Jr cheeseburger for $1.29. It's so small that it's only worth $1. They were very fast though.
California classic combo is overpriced at $5.99. Big hamburger is about $2. I got the halipeno burger since it's the only good deal. Food was good.
$3.49 2 cheeseburger meal and 10 piece for  $1.49. Good deals. Food was good and quick. Lobby was a bit messy.
Food was great, prices are just a tad high. Daily specials are $7.99 for a burrito and drink.
Meal deals are slightly overpriced at  $3.29. The box deal is also overpriced at  $5.99. The food was good and service was fast.

Don't come looking for a good deal, there aren't any. They don't have the  $3.49 2 cheeseburger meal like most other locations. I couldn't see the hot dog on the menu that other locations have for less than a dollar. I ended up getting the double whopper meal for  $8.49. That's almost enough for a buffet. Lol. The food was good and quick though.
Meal deals are slightly overpriced at  $3.19. $1 menu items are $1, unlike some locations. The food was good.
$8.99 lunch buffet including drink from 11-2 pm. Not the greatest price for a pizza buffet, but not bad. The pizza is good and they put out the the right amount, so it's always fresh.
The pizza isn't bad, but it's only worth $5, not the $7 they charge.  It was hot and ready. They don't take American express.
$10.99 for lunch buffet. Drinks included. Not bad, but not the best deal. I wasn't really impressed with the desserts, but the food was good.
$3.49 deal and 10 piece for $1.49 available here. Fast service and food was ok. Burgers tasted a little old. Extra dry bread.

location: 3831 E Craig RdNorth Las Vegas, NV 89030
reviewContent: Nuggets weren't great and the fries weren't either. Wait time was longer than usual. The 2 cheeseburger deal is a little more than before at $3.49, still a good value. 10 piece  $1.49 as usual.

location: 2101 Texas Star LnNorth Las Vegas, NV 89032
reviewContent: $12.99 Saturday night with a brand new players card. Not great on price. Food was alright, pizza wasn't great. Waitress was good and kept my drink full.
$7.49 lunch buffet is an alright deal, but drinks are overpriced at $2.49. I did like the big cups though. I wasn't really impressed with the quality of the food.
I couldn't find any good deal on the menu, but they were fast and the food was good. .......................................................
$3.29 deal and 10 piece for  $1.49 available here. Great deals. They were a bit slow, but accidentally gave me an extra fries.
They have some good deals and the food was good, but they must charge more for chicken. My 7.99 deal was 8.99.

4 for $4 available here. Great deal. The value menu prices aren't great though. Service was fast and food was good. Fries should have been salted right after they're pulled out, so the salt will stick. They weren't.
$3.29 deal and 10 piece $1.49 deal offered here. Great deals. Fast service and good food. Nice lobby too.
Real deal is $5 here. Big hamburgers $2. Not great on prices. They were slow to take my order, but quick to prepare it. Food was good. Lobby was clean.
Menu shows that meal deals are $2.59, but they ring up at $2.89. Dollar menu items ring up at $1.09. Speed wasn't great. Men's room was a mess. Food was good.
Prices are right here unlike many other taco bells. The wait time wasn't so good. I only ordered 2 small burritos and it took maybe 7-8 minutes. Food was good.
No 4 for $4 real deal here. The only decent deals I saw was California classic and halipeno burger meals. The food was good and service was fast.
They no longer have the $3.99 Jumbo deal. Food is good, and service was faster than usual. Most of the tables were messy.
reviewDate:
6/1/2017
            
                
    
        
    

                Updated review,5/20/2017
            
                Previous review,5/18/2017
            
                Previous review

reviewContent: Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday only  $8 with a players club card. The food is good. I've been here a few times now and have seen multiple plates that weren't cleaned properly.
4 for $4 is a great deal. Big hamburgers are $1.49. Food is good. Lobby is clean. I stop here almost every time I pass through.
Lunch buffet is a great deal. $6.49, but drinks are overpriced at $2.29 and $2.49, and if you get a water they give you a tiny little shot glass. The booth tables were all dirty. The food was good.
Food is good and service is too. Prices aren't good though. Real deal is $5. Big hamburger is  $1.99. California classic combo is $5.99. Priced higher than other locations.
Price isn't bad at about $9 for lunch with water, but drinks are overpriced. I came in just after 3:00, they weren't very busy and some of the food was a bit old.
4 for $4 available here. Great deal. Big hamburger is overpriced at $1.89 or $1.99......................
Food was good and service was fast. They don't offer the 4 for $4 real deal. California classic combo is still available for $5.

Food was good and service was too, but prices are not. They don't have the 4 for $4 real deal. I decided to try the new baby back rib burger combo... $9.99 for the regular single. The double and Angus are even more obviously. It was a tease. Kid's meal for buffet money? Wtf?

Lunch is priced very well around $8.49. I don't remember exactly. Drinks are about $1.69 more. Not too bad. It's your typical Chinese buffet like you'll find across the country. Food is good. Well worth the low price.
$3.29 deal is a steal. 10 piece nugget is also a good value. Service was very fast. Food was good.
4 for $4 real deal here. Great deal. Big hamburger  $1.99. Not great, not bad. Food was good, service was fast, lobby was clean.
They have a few good deals, but a small drink isn't one of them. $1.89... wtf? The breakfast burrito tortilla was dry and hard.

This place is very popular and crowded. I don't understand the hype. The burgers are good, but the fries aren't great. They don't have any good deals. Plan on paying about $7 and not getting enough to eat.

4 for $4 was great. They have a self serve drink machine now unlike other locations. They stop taking orders at the counter until the previous order is handed out. I really wish Wendy's would fix that problem.
I got the 1/2 lb cheeseburger. Really good, but not $8.99 good. Not quite enough to eat for the price. They were fast too.
They offer the 4 for $4 real deal, $5 California classic combo. Great deals. Fast service, clean lobby.
$14.99 on Saturday and Sunday. Overpriced. Drinks are $1.50, not too bad. The food is good, it's your typical Chinese buffet.
Meal deals $2.99. $1 menu items are $1, but $5 boxes are $5.99. Food is good and service is fast.

They have the 4 for $4 real deal. Big hamburgers are overpriced though at $2.49. They were pretty fast, but my double cheeseburger tasted like it had been sitting there a while. Bread was a bit dry and the meat wasn't warm enough to melt the cheese even a little bit.
$3.29 2 cheeseburger meal. $1.49 10 piece. Killer deals. Food is good, but they're slower than molasses.

They have a few great deals at the moment. 2 cheeseburger combo for $3.29, 10 piece for $1.49, a few small burgers for $1. They were fast. My rodeo cheeseburger didn't have cheese though. That was odd.

$7.99 for lunch and drinks are $1.59. Not bad. There wasn't a whole lot of food that I like personally, but they have all the typical Chinese food including sushi for those of you who like raw animals.
They have the 4 for $4 deal. Big hamburgers are $1.99. Not too bad, but not great. The service was a little slower than expected. The lobby was a bit messy.
Lunch buffet is priced right. I think it's  $7.99. Drinks are too expensive, pizza prices didn't look too great. The buffet was fresh, stocked, and clean. Good deal.

This place is a mad house at lunch time, even on Sunday. The lobby was a mess, the garbages are full, the tables were all dirty. They have the $4 deal though, that's what I came for. The big hamburger is overpriced.
Some of the food is a bit bland. I had a busser, but no waitress. Price isn't bad, $9.29 with water. Drinks are too much.
No $4 deal here, but they do have the 10 piece for  $1.49. Value menu isn't the best, but not horrible. Food was good and service was fast.
4 for $4 available at this locatation. $5 California classic combo too. Great deals. Fast service, clean lobby, good food. All good.

The service was quick, the food was good, the lobby was nice and clean. I wasn't really impressed with the prices. I got the #7 combo, triple cheeseburger for $9.59 + tax. It's only worth $6.99-$7.99. I couldn't find any good deal on the menu.
Pizza was good. They were offering the large 2 topping for $5.99 this week. Killer deal, but they charge extra for chicken.
They offer the  4 for  $4 at this locatation. Great deal, but other prices aren't really impressive. Service is fast, food is good. Drinks are as weak as any other Carl's Jr.

category:
Chicken Wings,
                    Fast Food,
                    Chicken Shop
reviewContent: Chicken was a tad dry, but still good. $5 boxes are a good value. They were extremely fast. My order was ready before I had my change. They don't accept American express cards.
4 for  $4 is offered at this locatation. Killer deal. Food was good. 8 minute wait time wasn't really impressive. I'll come back.
Good pizza, they screwed up the order and had to remake, but it was before I arrived, so the additional wait time wasn't too bad. The $7.99 large is $8.49 at this locatation. Wtf?
Fast service, good food. $1 menu items are  $1 and $5 box is $5 unlike some locations, but meal deals are  $3.69. Wtf?
Good food, good service, prices are right on some things, but the cravings deal is  $5.99.
No 4 for $4 here. California classic isn't too bad of a deal, but other than that prices aren't good. Service was fast, and food was good.
Lobby is clean, service was fast and accurate, food was good. Cravings menu is still a rip off and the self serve drink machine isn't working.
Prices are too high just like any other subway. They do have the steak and cheese footlong for  $6 for a limited time, but even that only does half the job. Food is good.
They have a 4 for $4, 10 piece for $1.49. Good deals. They're fast, and the food is good.
They're fast and the food is good, but their prices are too high. Typical truck stop prices. Meal deals  $4.19, $5 box is $5.69, $1 menu items are more than  $1.
They have the 4 for  $4 deal and the California classic combo for $5. Good deals. Service was very fast. Food was good.
Meal deals are $2.59. $5 box is $5 unlike some Taco Bells. $1 menu items are  $1 unlike some. Food is good.
No good deals, took about 10 minutes to make 2 sandwiches. Food wasn't too bad..............................................

I come here about once a year for their exclusive browned butter mizithra. It's really good, but their prices are ridiculous. I had that with a hearty portion and a water and it was over  $15 before tip. I wasn't impressed with the meal size either. They should have added another 25% at least.
The 4 for $4 is a great deal, but I wasn't impressed with any other prices. Wait time was normal, the food was good, the drinks are like any other Carl's Jr, watered down.
I got a good value with a link in my email. Took 14 minutes as expected. The pizza wasn't bad, but could have used more cheese and bacon.

Everything is overpriced. $5 boxes are $5.69 and $5.39. $3 meal deals are  $3.79. $1 limited time tacos are $1.29. Cravings menu items are way over  $1. Typical truck stop prices. The food was good though.

I went at dinner time and wasn't impressed with the prices. Pizza & salad 10.99 or the full menu for $13.99. Drinks are an extra  $2.49. The pizza was good. The crust is nice and buttery. Ice cream machine wasn't working

I visit Ontario often and have been curious about this place. I tried it today for lunch and the first time was the last time. The food isn't bad, but not great. It's the price that is so bad. $14.49 for weekday lunch. I assumed it included a drink since there are no drink prices on the board, but later found out they're another  $1.99. You have to look really close at your napkin box for the drink menu.
Regular prices didn't look great, but happy hour prices were alright. Food was good, service was fast, lobby was clean.
The food was good and they were fast, but my dbl cheese combo was about  $2 overpriced. Total was $9.36. Lol wtf?
Prices are right, they're quick, the lobby is clean, and the food is good. What more could you want?
They said guacamole was extra money, and boy they weren't kidding. $1.49 for a couple table spoons. Other than that the $5 deal was a good value. I'll go back, but won't be having guacamole.
The food was good, service was fast, price was right for my plan A, but I noticed the cravings deal is $1 overpriced.
The food was good. I don't see any good deals on the menu. The wait was 7 minutes. Not too bad, but not great.
The prices are right, the food was good, and they were fast. It was my first time here and I'll make sure to stop by in the future when I'm passing through
A decent buffet for little money. I go to the Bountiful location often and just tried this one. Great value and good eating.
They weren't very fast. The wait was probably 10 minutes and meal deals are over priced. At least their  $5 deal isn't  $6 like at some locations. The food was good and the place was clean.
Rabit's food isn't really my bag, but it was pretty good salad. I wasn't really impressed with the $11.99 dinner price, and that's with a water.
Good food and fast service. I'm not really impressed with the value menu prices, but the 4 for $4 is good.
Service was fast, food was good, lobby was mostly clean, but meal deals aren't priced right. The $5 box is though, unlike some Taco Bells.
The food was good, but prices are insane. I got a truckers discount to soften the blow, but I think taco bell still would have been a better value.
I wasn't expecting half the menu being breakfast at 2:30 in the afternoon, but the price was right with a truckers coupon. I'll come back.
They were fast, the pizza was good, the price wasn't bad, they should put more cheese on it though.

Prices aren't like they used to be. I came for breakfast and got 2 steak egg burritos and a coffee. The steak was a bit cold and the coffee was aged a little. Looking at other items on the menu, the prices are too damn high. Just use a coupon like I did.
Just like any other cicis, the quality isn't all that great, but the price is right. $5.99 with a water. Cokes are $1.89 I think.

location: 7430 Las Vegas Blvd SouthLas Vegas, NV 89123
reviewContent: Good food. Prices aren't great, but not ridiculous. The so called mild wings are actually very spicy.

Food was good. They no longer have the double cheese that I got the last couple years, but the philly was good too. Prices aren't too bad on food. I'm not sure about beers. We could watch about 7 or 8 different tvs, but they were all playing the same football game.

location: 3635 Las Vegas Blvd SLas Vegas, NV 89109
reviewContent: Very expensive. My $13 burger was only worth $4 and doesn't include a side. A Coke is $3.95 and comes in a fast food style cup. An $18 beer comes in a clear plastic glass. It looks cool, but very cheap. The water doesn't taste right. The burger was good and I could understand it being $6-7, since they're located here, but $13 is insane.
$8 for a large 3 topping is a pretty good value. I've ordered here many times and had no problems except this last time they forgot 1 of the toppings on 1 pizza. The other 1 was fine.

category:
Burgers,
                    Fast Food,
                    Ice Cream & Frozen Yogurt
reviewContent: The burger was pretty good. I don't really care for the fries. The wait time was 6-7 minutes. Prices aren't really good, but not too bad.
The food was good, the service was good, the prices are not so good. Sucks to see the $4 deal has gone up.
Had to wait a few minutes, but the pizza was fresh out of the oven. Little Ceasers isn't the best, but they are the cheapest. I'll be back.

Lunch was $10.99 and includes a beverage. After 3:00 they start packing up the food and my waitress was busy cleaning and stopped bringing drinks, so it's best to get there before 2:00. The food was great, the price was alright.
I was surprised to see a pizza buffet in the middle of the dessert. The food was pretty good. The price was OK at $8.99. I would come back if I ever pass through again.

Lunch was $9 with water, which isn't bad, but there wasn't a whole lot that I liked here. It's a typical Chinese buffet and I usually get a Chinese biscuit on every plate at these places, but they were too dried out and hard here. I came at a slow hour though.

location: 2121 E Craig RdNorth Las Vegas, NV 89030
reviewContent: Priced right at $10.99 for lunch. Most of the food was good, but the pizza looked like it was sitting out for an hour. I didnt even bother trying since there was a lot of other food that I like.
Lunch is $11.99. Dinner is $16.99. Lunch isn't too bad of a deal. The food is good. Dinner price is too damn high though and seafood day is much more than that.

Breakfast buffet was $9.99. The food wasn't bad, but nothing to get excited about. I went for breakfast thinking the price would be lower than lunch and it probably was, but still a bit high for the cheap food.
Lunch was $10.99 with a water. Drinks are $2.29 if I remember right. A bit too steep, but the food was good.
Service was fast, lobby was clean, and the food was good. Prices aren't so good. Typical for a truck stop though.

The grilled chicken combo is $5 for a limited time, which is a good value. I didnt see any other good values. With 1 cashier, the wait in line can take a little too long. Wendy's is known for that though. A self serve drink machine would be nice too. The food was good and the lobby was pretty clean. I always stop at taco bell next door, but decided to try this. Wasn't as good.

Friday dinner was $13.99. Way too much for a dive like this. Booth seats were torn up, the chicken wasn't good. There actually wasn't much that I liked. Each plate was fish, Chinese biscuit, pineapple, and potatoes. I tried a little eclair looking thing and it had a nasty aftertaste. The waiter was good though. He kept the refills coming.

I'm not from here, but I noticed this place has no shortage on crack heads. I had the misfortune of waiting in line to order behind a crack head trying to determine what his bum friend wanted him to order. Took a good 5 minutes. The food was good, some of the tables were messy, and the 4 for $4 is now 4 for $5. I didnt see any other good value so I got that.
I got the lunch special, $1 slices. Not a bad deal and they were fresh out of the oven.
The prices are right unlike some Taco Bells. Meal deals $2.89, $5 box is $5, $1 menu items are $1. Wait time was less than 3 minutes. The food was good and the lobby was clean. All good here.

There wasn't a whole lot of foods that I like, but I won't blame them for it since it is a Chinese joint. Each of my plates were almost the same... Salmon, Chinese biscuit, fries. They do have a lot of different kinds of chicken and fruits that I like though. The pizza wasn't looking good at all. Lunch was $8.99 +$1.99 drink if I remember right.
Wait time was a little longer than expected, but the food was good. They offer some good deals too, which is nice to see in any truck stop. 5 for $4 and 10 piece for $1.49. I got both.

I decided to eat here instead of Taco Bell today knowing they have $1 grilled dogs. After ordering I waited for my # to be called. Somehow mine was skipped, so after 16 minutes I asked if it was still coming. 3 minutes later I got it. They gave me a free pie for waiting. The food was good.
They offer some good deals like 5 for $4. 10 piece for $1.49. Hotdogs for .99. The food was good and service was fast, but the lobby was looking neglected. 90% of tables were dirty.
Typical truck stop taco bell prices. Meal deals $3.99, $5 box is $6, value menu items $1.29. Still beats subway though. Food was good and service was fast, just a bit overpriced.

I couldn't find a good value on the menu. I ordered the 5 chicken strips for $7 and it didn't come with sauce. It was good chicken, but only worth $5. I've never stopped here before and I don't think I will in the future. Wasn't good or bad overall.

I was happy to see their remodel was done, so I wouldn't have to overpay at taco bell across the road. The food was as good as expected. There was a 7-8 minute wait though. I always order the 4 for $4 and a 10 piece, both of which are a great deal. I will definitely be back when I'm in the area.

I've been traveling up and down I-5 often and I usually stop in Lost Hills for Taco Bell, but decided to stop here today to see what I'm missing. Prices are through the roof here. It's expected at truck stops, but not to this extent. Meal deals  $4.19, beefy fritos  $1.99, cheesy bean and rice $2.49. Wtf? The $5 box was $5.69 (surprised it wasn't more) so I got that. So why are they worthy of a second star? Well, their lobby was clean and up to date and the food was good. If I'm ever shut down at this TA I'll just walk to Carl's Jr.

$9 lunch buffet and it includes a drink. Very good value. Unfortunately I have to pay $3 to park my truck across the road, otherwise I would stop here often. Fish was great, 3 different chickens were great. Waiter was good too.

Service was fast, food was good, the lobby was nice and clean, employees were great. I think the manager was high on something when he/she priced meal deals at $3.79. I had to go with plan B, the $5 box.

Each weekday has a slightly different menu. The food is good and the drinks are included. The price went up recently, so the value may not be quite as good as Golden Corral, but I always look forward to eating here.

Cheapest buffet in the area. Just make sure to go during busy hours or the quality will be horrible. They have many different pizzas to choose from. Too many during slow hours. It's often a mad house after 6 pm with so many inconsiderate people lolly gagging at the food bar and drink machines. Half of them are fat as H and I've even had people steal my booth a few times when I got up for a new plate. Besides pizza they have pasta, salad, and fruit. Great value, decent food.
Decent prices like any other BK. Service was fast. Lobby was clean and very modern. All good.
Tastes like donuts from any grocery store, but costs more. I got a bear claw and a blueberry filled for $3.40 with tax. Not outrageous, but not good either.

Monday dinner was $12.99, which isn't good, but not insane either. The quality is comparable to Golden Corral. I like to see salmon, lasagna, Mac and cheese, and enchiladas at buffets, but none of which were there Monday.
Meal deals only $2.79 here, but I got the $5 box this time. Both are a good value. Food was good, service was a bit slow. 8 minute wait
4 for $4 was a good value and small frosties are only 50 cents for a limited time. Good deal. Food was good service was fast.

Good to see meal deals even lower than $3. The menu showed $2.79, but rang up for $2.89. $1 menu was good too. Service was fast, food was good. I sat right next to a wall and noticed ants were crawling on the wall.
The food was good, it was clean, service was fast. The meal deals that I usually order are slightly overpriced at this locatation.
I was the only customer in the lobby around 4:00, so service was fast. Lobby was pretty clean, and they offer a $5 meal. The Whoppurrito meal. Good value.
I get a medium for $6 with a link in my email. Great deal and as good of quality as any pizza hut. I was eating here often before my job took me out of town and it's always been good.

I've always avoided this locatation and went to burger King across the street knowing the prices are cost plus 30 percent. Now burger king's lobby is closed for remodel, so came here. $3 meal deals are $4, $5 box is $6, and the dollar menu is more of a $1.29 menu. They were fast and the food was good though.

I knew my total should have been about $6.40, but he said $9.28. I decided to just eat whatever it was he rang up. He rung up 2 beef burritos rather than the 2 beefy fritos that I ordered. They were $2.39 each and they're only worth  $1. The lobby was clean, but very outdated. A remodel is about ten years overdue. I'll be back in, but I won't be having beef burritos.

I came in at a bad time when they were very busy and my order took 21 minutes. Small meal deals are $3.99 at this locatation, wtf? I don't know what the general manager is smoking, but it's very potent. At least they do have the $5 box, which is an OK deal. The food was good.
4 for $4 deal here. Good value, good service, good food, clean lobby. I don't have a stupid story like other reviewers, but my review has to be long with all this nonsense.
$3 meal deals are a good value and dollar menu items. Great service, good food. I'll be back next time I'm in the area.

$5 Super Star combo. Good value, good food, clean lobby, good everything. I don't have a stupid story like other reviewers, but I have to write more BS for my review to count as a review, so here it is.

category:
Fast Food,
                    Chicken Wings,
                    Chicken Shop
reviewContent: 5-10 minute wait for chicken tenders, lobby was a bit messy, food was good.I don't have a stupid story like other reviewers, but I have to write some BS, otherwise my review is only a tip. So there's some BS.
